{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"45fe3ab2-bf6e-4568-8911-ebf61ef74fad","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_H9mfdITdfVJP61dE4SXf2N","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9134339cde2d4376bb8fc41759e65134/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9134339cde2d4376bb8fc41759e65134/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"56c51f3e-acda-4518-b0dd-6cc29f724216","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, the file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order.\n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs`\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":461,"requestId":"280E:926CA:1AFB355:1E0BD70:69FA8FDF"},"id":"cb13930e-917c-435a-b22f-aa818b6e72a7","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:38.996Z","parentId":"bb6588c0-9997-462a-ab37-aec34bb7dcb6"}
